Key Match Events: Craig Young took two crucial wickets in one over of Babar Azam and Azam Khan
Andrew Balbirnie and Harry Tector put on a 75-run partnership
Andrew Balbirnie played a counter-attacking innings (77 off 55 balls)
Curtis Campher took a leg bye off the penultimate ball of the match to seal the victory
Post-Match Reflections: George Dockrell was caught out by Fakhar Zaman
Netizens reacted strongly to Ireland's win, calling it the worst team ever
There were discussions about including teams like Ireland and Netherlands in mainstream cricket
Some suggested giving back the captaincy to Shaheen Shah Afridi
Miscellaneous Highlights: Ireland's first T-20 win over Pakistan in 17 years
Pakistan 1-0 down in the three-match T20 series
The match was played at Clontarf Cricket Club in Dublin
The loss comes ahead of the upcoming T20 World Cup
